ComicInfo.Summary:
Special 100Th issue!!! Only the 229Th comic book in history to reach the 100 issue mark!!! With a little time spent on Zaltair, The Femforce begin to learn it is a strange place, indeed. Somehow, it changes people. The Black Commando is completly sane, and Nightveil retains her magical abilities, even without her Cloak Of Darkness. Tara can grow to titanic heights, taller than any giantess ever seen, yet She-Cat gets Sehkmet's werecat form, but her own intellect. And Stardust-poor Stardust loses her powers altogether. While it appears the FF have fallen right in the middle of a civil war between the Zaltair and the Preen, it's actually more like a game- only the casualties are real! Ms.Victory and Kinetics make it down to the surface just in time for the Zaltairian's big win. Kinetics is repowered, Mitch Cameron regains control of his Bolt half, and The Black Commando emplores NV to stay on Zaltair with him. When an urgent distress call to Earth comes to Nightveil from Azagoth, the girls realize they must return immediately. When they land, they suddenly learn who the other player in the cosmic chess game that controlled there Zaltairian adventure was, when they come face to face with-...!!! "Full Circle" is written by Bill Black, drawn by Brad Gorby, and inked by Mark Heike. It guest stars Dr. Ostrowski and his granddaughter, The Shimmerer and General Enrog. It has some extreme giant woman scenes with Tara; superb GTS. The book has a color cover by Brad Gorby and Mark Heike. Interiors are black and white with graytones, Standard comic book formay, with an extra-long, 32-page story.
